{"title_page": "U.S. state and local government response to the 2020 coronavirus pandemic", "text_new": "{{short description|U.S. state and local government response to 2020 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{Current event|2=current pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n[[File:COVID-19 outbreak USA stay-at-home order county map.svg|thumb|right|300px|States, territories, and counties that issued a [[stay-at-home order]]\n{{legend|#045a8d|Came into effect before March 22}}\n{{legend|#2b8cbe|Came into effect before March 29}}\n{{legend|#74a9cf|Came into effect before April 5}}\n{{legend|#a6bddb|Came into effect before April 12}}\n'''[[Commons:Data:Stay-at-home orders in the United States.map|Full map including municipalities]]''']]\n\n'''State, territorial, tribal, and local governments have responded to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States]]''' with various declarations of emergency, closure of schools and public meeting places, and other restrictions intended to slow the progression of the virus.\n\n{{TOC US states\n|before=[[#State level regulations|State level regulations]]\n|DC=yes\n|PR=yes\n|after=[[#Territories|Territories]]\n* [[#Indian nations|Indian nations]]\n* [[#Further reading|Further reading]]\n|seealso=yes\n|extlinks=yes\n|refs=yes\n}}\n__NOTOC__\n\n== State-level regulations==\n\nThis is a list of regulations that were imposed at the state level, restricting activities and closing facilities as a result of the pandemic. Many counties and municipal jurisdictions have imposed more stringent regulations.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style = \"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\"| State/territory\n! rowspan=\"2\"| State of emergency declared\n! rowspan=\"2\"| [[Stay-at-home order|Stay at home ordered]]\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Gatherings banned\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Out-of-state travel restrictions\n! colspan=\"4\"| Closures ordered\n! rowspan=\"2\"| Sources\n|-\n! Schoo