ss Point under curfew, shelter in place order beginning Saturday|publisher=[[WLOX]]|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020|url=https://www.wlox.com/2020/03/28/mayor-king-moss-point-under-curfew-shelter-place-order-beginning-saturday/}}</ref> after a previous order was voided by Governor Reeves but a new executive order permitted such a declaration.<ref>{{cite web |title=Immediate Release Moss Point Executive Order Voided by Governor |url=https://cityofmosspoint.org/AlertCenter.aspx?AID=Immediate-Release-Moss-Point-Executive-O-22 |website=Moss Point, MS |accessdate=29 March 2020}}</ref>\n* March 31{{snd}}Governor Reeves issued a shelter-in-place order for [[Lauderdale County, Mississippi|Lauderdale County]] effective March 31 through April 14.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gov. Reeves issues shelter-in-place order for Lauderdale County|publisher=[[WJTV]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020|url=https://www.wjtv.com/health/coronavirus/gov-reeves-issues-shelter-in-place-order-for-lauderdale-county/}}</ref> [[Meridian, Mississippi|Meridian]] responded with its own shelter-in-place order.<ref>{{cite news|title=Meridian issues second executive order: Shelter-in-Place|publisher=[[WTOK-TV]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020|url=https://www.wtok.com/content/news/Meridian-issues-second-executive-order-Shelter-in-Place-569264831.html}}</ref>\n* April 1{{snd}}Governor Reeves issued a statewide shelter-in-place order effective April 3.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reeves issues statewide shelter-in-place order|first=Tim|last=Reeves|work=[[The Vicksburg Post]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://www.vicksburgpost.com/2020/04/01/reeves-issues-statewide-shelter-in-place-order/}}</ref> Earlier, [[Bay St. Louis, Mississippi|Bay St. Louis]], [[Biloxi, Mississippi|Biloxi]], [[Gulfport, Mississippi|Gulfport]], [[D'Iberville, Mississippi|D'Iberville]], [[Long Beach, Mississippi|Long Beach]], and [[Pascagoula, Mississippi|Pascagoula]] issued curfews and ad