i|Kansas City]] and [[Belton, Missouri|Belton]] issued stay-at-home orders on March 22.<ref name=\"KMBC Belton\">{{cite news |title='Stay-at-home' order issued for Clay and Platte counties in Missouri, Leavenworth County in Kansas |publisher=[[KMBC-TV]] |date=March 22, 2020 |accessdate=March 22, 2020 |url=https://www.kmbc.com/article/stay-at-home-order-issued-for-belton-leavenworth-county-kansas-platte-county-missouri-because-of-covid-19-outbreak-coronavirus/31875442}}</ref>\n\n[[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]] and [[St. Louis County, Missouri|St. Louis County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective March 23 to April 22.<ref>{{cite news|title=St. Louis City, County 'stay-at-home' orders go into effect Monday. Here's what you need to know|first=Nicole |last=Sanders|publisher=[[KMOV]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020|url=https://www.kmov.com/news/st-louis-city-county-stay-at-home-orders-go-into/article_4119cbdc-6b91-11ea-8be5-2b26bdc82689.html}}</ref> [[St. Charles County, Missouri|St. Charles County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective March 24.<ref>{{cite news|title=St. Charles County issues stay-at-home order starting Tuesday|first=Joe|last=Millitzer|publisher=[[KPLR-TV]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020|url=https://fox2now.com/news/missouri/st-charles-county-issues-stay-at-home-order-taking-effect-tuesday/}}</ref> [[Jefferson County, Missouri|Jefferson County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective from March 24 through April 23.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jefferson County issues stay-at-home order due to coronavirus concerns|first=Sam|last=Clancy|publisher=[[KSDK]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020|url=https://www.ksdk.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/jefferson-county-stay-home-order-coronavirus/63-5e26a6cd-3e5c-4825-ba44-525d5e830858}}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, [[Columbia, Missouri|Columbia]] and surrounding [[Boone County, Missouri|Boone County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective March 25 through April 24.<ref>{{cite news|