om/news/gov-sisolak-to-make-announcement-about-covid-19 Nevada Gov. Steve Sisolak declares state of emergency after additional coronavirus cases] [[KTNV]]</ref>\n\nOn March 17, Governor [[Steve Sisolak]] ordered all non-essential businesses closed for 30 days.<ref>[https://www.reviewjournal.com/business/casinos-gaming/nevada-casinos-closing-for-30-days-following-state-order-1984236/ Nevada casinos closing for 30 days following state order]</ref>\n\nOn March 24, Governor Sisolak banned the use of anti-malaria drugs for COVID-19 treatment, notably [[chloroquine]] and [[hydroxychloroquine]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://lasvegassun.com/news/2020/mar/24/sisolak-bars-malaria-drugs-for-coronavirus-patient/|title=Sisolak bars malaria drugs for coronavirus patients|work=Las Vegas Sun|date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 1, Governor Sisolak issued a statewide stay-at-home order effective until April 30.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sisolak issues stay at home order|first1=Bill|last1=Dentzer|first2=Colton|last2=Lochhead|work=[[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://www.reviewjournal.com/news/politics-and-government/nevada/sisolak-issues-stay-at-home-order-1996415/}}</ref>\n\n==New Hampshire==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in New Hampshire}}\n* March \u2013 State of Emergency, School closings<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nhpr.org/post/coronavirus-update-nh-schools-ordered-close-3-weeks-covid-19-cases-rise-13 |title=Coronavirus Update: N.H. Schools Ordered To Close For 3 Weeks, As COVID-19 Cases Rise to 13 |first=NHPR |last=Staff |website=nhpr.org}}</ref>\n* March 26{{snd}}Governor [[Chris Sununu]] issues a statewide stay-at-home order effective March 27 until May 4.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gov. Chris Sununu issues stay-at-home order for New Hampshire|first=Kirk|last=Enstrom|publisher=[[WMUR-TV]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020|url=https://www.wmur.com/article/live-at-3-sununu-gives-upd