 dental procedures will be pushed back until after April 7.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://oklahoman.com/article/5658491/stitt-to-implement-safer-at-home-policy |title=Coronavirus in Oklahoma: Stitt announces 'safer-at-home' policy |website=The Oklahoman |date=March 24, 2020 |access-date=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n* March 28{{snd}}[[Oklahoma City]] and [[Tulsa, Oklahoma|Tulsa]] issued shelter-in-place orders effective March 28 through April 16.<ref>{{cite news|title=Oklahoma City Mayor Holt orders residents to 'Shelter in Place' to prevent spread of coronavirus|first=Hicham|last=Raache|publisher=[[KFOR-TV]]|date=March 28, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020|url=https://kfor.com/health/coronavirus/oklahoma-city-mayor-holt-orders-residents-to-shelter-in-place-to-prevent-spread-of-coronavirus/}}</ref>\n* March 30{{snd}}[[Stillwater, Oklahoma|Stillwater]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective March 30 through April 16.<ref>{{cite news|title=City of Stillwater issues shelter in place order|first=Kaylee|last=Douglas|publisher=[[KFOR-TV]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020|url=https://kfor.com/news/local/city-of-stillwater-issues-shelter-in-place-order/}}</ref> [[Edmond, Oklahoma|Edmond]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective March 30 through April 16.<ref>{{cite news|title=City of Edmond issues shelter in place order due to coronavirus|first=Kaylee|last=Douglas|publisher=[[KFOR-TV]]|date=March 30, 2020|accessdate=March 30, 2020|url=https://kfor.com/news/local/city-of-edmond-issues-shelter-in-place-order-due-to-coronavirus/}}</ref>\n* March 31{{snd}}[[Lawton, Oklahoma|Lawton]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective April 1.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shelter-in-place order, city-wide curfew issued in Lawton|publisher=[[KFDX-TV]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020|url=https://www.texomashomepage.com/news/local-news/shelter-in-place-order-issued-in-lawton/}}</ref> [[Broken Arrow, Oklahoma|Broken Arrow]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective April 1.<ref>{