s to stay home|publisher=[[WTAE-TV]]|agency=Associated Press|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://www.wtae.com/article/pennsylvania-stay-at-home-order-statewide-coronavirus/32008159}}</ref>\n\n==Puerto Rico==\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Puerto Rico#Government response}}On March 12, Governor V\u00e1zquez declared a state of emergency and activated the National Guard. She stated that National Guard personnel will be stationed at the Luis Mu\u00f1oz Mar\u00edn International Airport and the [[Port of San Juan]] to screen arriving passengers for symptoms.<ref name=\":03\">{{cite web |url=https://www.militarytimes.com/news/coronavirus/2020/03/12/governor-of-puerto-rico-declares-emergency-activates-national-guard-in-response-to-coronavirus/ |title=Governor of Puerto Rico declares emergency, activates National Guard in response to coronavirus |last=Gresik |first=Dylan |date=March 13, 2020 |website=Military Times |language=en-US|access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, Puerto Rico public schools were closed for 14 days.<ref name=\":32\">{{cite web |url=https://www.foxbusiness.com/lifestyle/first-coronavirus-cases-in-puerto-rico |title=First coronavirus cases seen in Puerto Rico |date=March 14, 2020 |website=Associated Press |language=en-US|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 15, V\u00e1zquez issued an island-wide curfew through March 30 and closed all businesses not involved in food sales, medicine, or banking.<ref name=\"END Toque de Queda\">{{cite web |url=https://www.elnuevodia.com/noticias/locales/nota/wandavazquezdecretatoquedequedaparatodopuertoricoparacontenerelcoronavirus-2552934/ |title=Wanda V\u00e1zquez decreta toque de queda para todo Puerto Rico para contener el coronavirus [Wanda V\u00e1zquez declares curfew for all of Puerto Rico to contain coronavirus] |date=March 15, 2020 |website=El Nuevo Dia |language=es-pr|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Rhode Island==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Rhode Island}}\n* March 9, Governor [[Gina Raimondo]] declares a state of emergency.<ref>{{cite news |last=Miller |first=G. Wayne |date=March 9, 2020 |title=Raimondo declares state of emergency in R.I. over coronavirus |url=https://www.providencejournal.com/news/20200309/raimondo-declares-state-of-emergency-in-ri-over-coronavirus |work=Providence Journal |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n* March 13, Springbrook students self-quarantine after a Utah Jazz player gives autograph to one who tested positive;<ref>{{cite news |last=Doiron |first=Sarah |date=March 13, 2020 |title=Police: Westerly child with COVID-19 received autograph from infected Jazz player during Celtics game |url=https://www.wpri.com/health/coronavirus/police-westerly-child-with-covid-19-received-autograph-from-infected-jazz-player-during-celtics-game/ |work=WPRI |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref> \n*March 16, public schools are closed onward.<ref>{{cite news |last=Nesi |first=Ted |date=March 13, 2020 |title=RI public schools closed next week; 9 new coronavirus cases identified |url=https://www.wpri.com/health/coronavirus/friday-afternoon-coronavirus-update-rhode-island/ |work=WPRI |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n*March 17, Bars and dine-in restaurants closed, crowds of 25 or more people banned.<ref>{{cite news |last=Miller |first=G. Wayne |date=March 16, 2020 |title=Raimondo shutting dine-in restaurants, bars for 2 weeks; 'community spread' of virus now seen in R.I. |url=https://www.providencejournal.com/news/20200316/raimondo-shutting-dine-in-restaurants-bars-for-2-weeks-rsquocommunity-spreadrsquo-of-virus-now-seen-in-ri |work=Providence Journal |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref>\n*March 24{{snd}}[[New Shoreham, Rhode Island|New Shoreham]] issues a shelter-in-place order for [[Block Island]] effective March 24 through April 15.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shelter-in-place order issued for Block Island|first=Shaun|last=Towne|publisher=[[WPRI-TV]]|date=March 24, 2020|acces