arrant, Collin counties issue 'stay at home' order to stop spread of COVID-19|first1=Tasha|last1=Tsiaperas|first2=Lauren|last2=Zakalik|first3=Charlotte|last3=Huffman|publisher=[[WFAA]]|date=March 24, 2020|accessdate=March 24, 2020|url=https://www.wfaa.com/article/news/health/coronavirus/dallas-fort-worth-orders-stay-home-coronavirus/287-f1a078d1-4324-4933-9cec-2087201ba591}}</ref>\n\n[[Waco, Texas|Waco]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective March 23 initially for seven days; surrounding [[McLennan County, Texas|McLennan County]] soon followed with its own order effective for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|title=Waco orders shelter in place; commissioners extend order to county|work=[[Waco Tribune-Herald]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020|url=https://www.wacotrib.com/news/government/waco-orders-shelter-in-place-commissioners-extend-order-to-county/article_e6225b23-6d3f-5ce1-b6d5-7486ee1bebae.html}}</ref> [[Corsicana, Texas|Corsicana]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective March 25 through April 8.<ref>{{cite news|title=Corsicana declares shelter in place order|first=Michael|last=Kormos|work=[[Corsicana Daily Sun]]|date=March 23, 2020|accessdate=March 23, 2020|url=https://www.corsicanadailysun.com/covid-19/corsicana-declares-shelter-in-place-order/article_c3daa4de-6d6b-11ea-99ff-5336107bb8b9.html}}</ref> On March 24, [[Navarro County, Texas|Navarro County]] extended this order to the whole county.<ref>{{cite news|title=Navarro County issues \"Stay Home, Stay Safe\" order|date=March 24, 2020|url=https://www.corsicanadailysun.com/covid-19/navarro-county-issues-stay-home-stay-safe-order/article_dcbfc752-6e03-11ea-b5d8-eb20c398a391.html}}</ref>\n\nOn March 23, [[Brazos County, Texas|Brazos County]], in conjunction with [[Bryan, Texas|Bryan]] and [[College Station, Texas|College Station]], issued a shelter-in-place order effective March 24 until April 7.<ref>{{cite news|title=Brazos County issues shelter in place order|publisher=[[KWKT-TV]]|date=March 23, 2