nty, Texas|Hopkins County]] issued a shelter-in-place order described as a \"stay safe at home\" order.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hopkins County Issues New Declaration Of Disaster|work=EastTexasRadio.com|publisher=East Texas Broadcasting|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://easttexasradio.com/hopkins-county-issues-new-declaration-of-disaster/}}</ref> [[Cass County, Texas|Cass County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective April 2 through April 30.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cass County judge issues stay-at-home order|first=Karl|last=Richter|work=[[Texarkana Gazette]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://www.texarkanagazette.com/news/texarkana/story/2020/apr/01/cass-county-judge-issues-stay--home-order/822801/}}</ref> [[Lufkin, Texas|Lufkin]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective April 2 until further notice.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lufkin officials adopt 'stay-at-home' order at request of medical community, establish curfew|first=Stephanie|last=Frazier|publisher=[[KTRE]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://www.ktre.com/2020/04/01/lufkin-officials-adopt-stay-at-home-order-request-medical-community-establish-curfew/}}</ref> [[Victoria County, Texas|Victoria County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective April 2 until April 30.<ref>{{cite news|title=Victoria County issues stay-at-home order|first=Ciara|last=McCarthy|work=[[The Victoria Advocate]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://www.victoriaadvocate.com/covid-19/victoria-county-issues-stay-at-home-order/article_f5fbf718-7443-11ea-9c6a-1f122bb555bc.html}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, Governor Abbott clarified that his executive order is a stay-at-home order.<ref name=\"Chron Foxhall\">{{cite news|title=Gov. Greg Abbott's statewide stay-home order, explained|first=Taylor|last=Goldenstein|work=[[Houston Chronicle]]|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.houstonchronicle.com/news/article/Gov-Greg-Abbott-s-statewide-stay-home-order-15175150.php}}</ref> [[Anderson County, Texas|Anderson County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective until further notice.<ref>{{cite news|title=Anderson County issues stay-at-home order|first=Giselle|last=Chavez|work=KYTX|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.cbs19.tv/article/news/local/anderson-county-issues-stay-at-home-order/501-c32a564b-5903-4ee5-8ab5-2c468f0c8f72}}</ref> [[Pampa, Texas|Pampa]] and surrounding [[Gray County, Texas|Gray County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective through April 8.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stay-at-home directive issued in Pampa, Gray County|first=Matthew|last=Watkins|publisher=[[KVII-TV]]|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020|url=https://abc7amarillo.com/news/local/stay-at-home-directive-issued-in-pampa-gray-county}}</ref> [[Brownfield, Texas|Brownfield]] issued a stay-at-home order effective April 3 until April 16.<ref>{{cite news|title=City of Brownfield issues Stay At Home order|publisher=[[KCBD]]|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.kcbd.com/2020/04/02/city-brownfield-issues-stay-home-order/}}</ref> Surrounding [[Terry County, Texas|Terry County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective April 3 until further notice.<ref>{{cite news|title=Stay at home/stay safe order (COVID-19)|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020|url=https://county.org/TAC/media/TACMedia/Legal/Declarations/County-Terry-3rd-Ratification-Stay-at-home-order-40220.pdf}}</ref> [[Matagorda County, Texas|Matagorda County]] issued a shelter-in-place order effective April 2 until further notice.<ref>{{cite news|title=Matagorda County orders mandatory shelter-in-place to reduce spread of coronavirus|publisher=[[KPRC-TV]]|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.click2houston.com/health/2020/04/03/matagorda-county-orders-mandatory-shelter-in-place-to-reduce-spread-of-coronavirus/}}</ref>\n\nOn April 3, [[Comal County, Texas|Comal County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective through April 30.<ref>{{ci