eeks.<ref>{{cite news|title=Charleston City Council approves 'stay at home' ordinance with broad exceptions for businesses|first1=Mikaela|last1=Porter|first2=Thad|last2=Moore|work=[[The Post and Courier]]|date=March 25, 2020|accessdate=March 25, 2020|url=https://www.postandcourier.com/health/covid19/charleston-city-council-approves-stay-at-home-ordinance-with-broad/article_0a29c94e-6de7-11ea-84b1-c3369b331f03.html}}</ref>\n\nOn March 26, [[Columbia, South Carolina|Columbia]] issued a stay-at-home order effective March 29 for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|title=Columbia adopts ordinance to stop spread of coronavirus|first=Stephen K.|last=Benjamin|authorlink=Stephen K. Benjamin|work=[[The State (newspaper)|The State]]|date=March 26, 2020|accessdate=March 26, 2020|url=https://www.thestate.com/news/coronavirus/article241529271.html}}</ref> [[Williamsburg County, South Carolina|Williamsburg County]] issued a stay-at-home order effective March 27 for 14 days.<ref>{{cite news|title=County leaders issue 'stay at home' order for Williamsburg County|first=Ray|last=Rivera|publisher=[[WCSC-TV]]|date=March 27, 2020|accessdate=March 27, 2020|url=https://www.live5news.com/2020/03/27/officials-issue-stay-home-order-williamsburg-county/}}</ref>\n\nOn April 1, [[Mount Pleasant, South Carolina|Mount Pleasant]] issued a stay-at-home order effective April 2 until April 15.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mount Pleasant issues 'Stay at Home' order, stops short-term rentals|publisher=[[WCIV]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 1, 2020|url=https://wpde.com/news/local/mount-pleasant-mayor-expected-to-issue-stay-at-home-order-tuesday}}</ref>\n\nOn April 6, South Carolina governer Henry McMaster issued a statewide \"home or work\" order which goes into effect Tuesday at 5 p.m.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/public-global-health/491431-south-carolina-issues-home-or-work-order|title=South Carolina issues 'home or work' order|last=Coleman|first=Justine|date=2020-04-06|website=TheHil